Mexican Stocks: Cemex, Industrias Penoles, Telmex

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-07-14T21:43:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-14/mexican-stocks-cemex-industrias-penoles-telefonos-de-mexico.html
(Corrects date when Carlos Robles Miaja will take over as
Telmex CFO from Adolfo Cerezo Perez in fourth paragraph)  The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index fell 0.2 percent at 36,164.61.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO MM), the largest cement maker in the
Americas, declined 1.5 percent to 9.32 pesos after Federal
Reserve Chairman  Ben S. Bernanke  said the U.S. central bank is
not prepared “at this point” to take action to stimulate the
economy. The  United States  accounted for 18 percent of Cemex’s
sales in 2010.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, rose 1.9 percent to 486.08 pesos as silver
futures for September delivery gained and  Fresnillo Plc (FRES) , the
world’s largest primary silver producer, said second-quarter
output rose 7.2 percent to a record. Production included 906,000
ounces from the Silverstream agreement, an accord between
Penoles and Fresnillo. Penoles has gained in six consecutive
trading days, reaching new all-time highs.  Telefonos de Mexico SAB (TELMEXL MM) gained 1 percent to
9.56 pesos as Mexico’s largest fixed-line phone and internet
provider said Carlos Robles Miaja will serve as the company’s
chief financial officer starting Aug. 15. He will replace Adolfo Cerezo Perez, the company said yesterday after the close of
trading.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York at 
